# <%= it.displayName %>

<%= it.description %>

Generated by [MCP Tool Generator](https://github.com/example/mcp-tool-generator) using `mcp==1.27.1` (FastMCP).

## Quick start

```bash
uv sync
cp .env.example .env
uv run server.py
```

The MCP server starts on port <%= it.port %> and exposes the `<%= it.mcpEndpoint %>` endpoint.

## Connecting to Claude Desktop

Add to `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`:

**Option A — mcp-remote (works with all Claude Desktop versions):**

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<%= it.serverName %>": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote", "http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>"]
    }
  }
}
```

**Option B — native URL (recent Claude Desktop versions):**

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<%= it.serverName %>": {
      "url": "http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>"
    }
  }
}
```

## Connecting to Claude Code

```bash
claude mcp add --transport http <%= it.serverName %> http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>
```

## Connecting to Cursor

Add to `~/.cursor/mcp.json` (global) or `.cursor/mcp.json` (project-local):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<%= it.serverName %>": {
      "url": "http://localhost:<%= it.port %><%= it.mcpEndpoint %>"
    }
  }
}
```

